My meme

# First cat meme
first_cat <- image_read("https://img.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeed-static/static/2023-04/4/1/asset/59fe9b1748b2/sub-buzz-788-1680571929-1.png?downsize=700:*&output-format=auto&output-quality=auto") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# Second cat meme
second_cat <- image_read("https://www.boredpanda.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/104-6329b53c8c836__700.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# First picture with text
first_text <- image_blank(width = 500,
                         height = 500,
                         color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Me:",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# Second picture with text
second_text <- image_blank(width = 500,
                           height = 500,
                           color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Me as well:",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# Combine my cat meme with the picture with text
combination_meme <- c(first_text, first_cat, second_text, second_cat) 

#Creating a png
final_meme <- image_append(combination_meme)
image_write(final_meme, "my_meme.png")
# Creating a animation
meme_gif <- image_animate(combination_meme, fps = 1)

image_write(meme_gif, "my_animation.gif")

Learning reflection

An important idea that I learned from module 1 is write the codes to create a png and gif by using R Studio. Before I taking stats 220 course I never thought that I can use R to create a picture and an animation. One thing that related to Data Technologies that I am curious is data storage. I am interesting on data storage is because data storage is essential for data science students entering fields where data plays a significant role. Whether studying business, science, or technology, data storage ensures information preservation, accessibility, and security. It supports scalability, disaster recovery, regulatory compliance, and facilitates data analysis.
